Feature: Strategic Gaps — From Knowledge to Operationalization

  As a community translating wiki knowledge into action
  I want to close the gaps between what's known and what's operational
  So that the knowledge graph produces measurable regenerative outcomes

  Background:
    Given the wiki contains 17 sources and 11 concepts defining the community knowledge base
    And the synthesis identifies what the wiki knows but has not yet operationalized
    And the strategic gaps represent the translation layer from knowledge to action

  Scenario: Operationalizing proof-of-regeneration
    Given proof-of-regeneration creates real-world ecological verification
    When rewards unlock only after ecological outcomes are verified
    Then regenerative practices are incentivized through measurable results
    And the feedback loop connects community action to ecological state
    And the system operates without centralized verification authority

  Scenario: Building the civilizational operating system
    Given the meta-layer connects knowledge retrieval, autonomous action, governance decisions, and regenerative feedback
    When the community builds this meta-layer
    Then it operates as a civilizational OS for communities
    And no single existing project has named or built this layer
    And the gap between components is the absence of this meta-layer

  Scenario: Connecting intelligence architecture to governance
    Given MST-Polcompball governance spec provides the governance layer without intelligence architecture
    And Goertzel's seminar provides the cognitive substrate without governance layer
    When the community bridges these two projects
    Then neither lacks the other's capabilities
    And the community addresses what it means to run both while developing regenerative infrastructure

  Scenario: Translating 12 thesis statements into testable behaviors
    Given the synthesis produces 12 convergent thesis statements
    When each thesis is expressed as a scenario with Given/When/Then
    Then each behavior is testable against community outcomes
    And the wiki's knowledge produces actionable specifications
    And the community moves from synthesis to execution

  Scenario: Offline-first knowledge retrieval under total internet blackout
    Given P2P/offline-resilient operation is required for total internet blackout scenario
    When the community builds knowledge infrastructure
    Then Syncthing maintains P2P sync across edge nodes
    And local knowledge retrieval continues without cloud dependency
    And the system degrades gracefully under network partition

  Scenario: Connecting Ostrom's 8 principles to digital commons governance
    Given Ostrom's principles are empirically grounded for physical commons
    When the community applies them to digital knowledge commons
    Then the same principles produce successful self-governance at digital scale
    And boundary rules, congruence, collective-choice arrangements, monitoring, graduated sanctions, conflict-resolution mechanisms, and recognized rights to organize are all implemented digitally
    And the digital commons avoids the tragedy of the digital commons

  Scenario: Agent skills for regenerative community operations
    Given agent skills package institutional knowledge for AI coding assistants
    When the community defines regenerative practices as skills
    Then agents execute with community-aligned behavior across all operations
    And the knowledge layer translates directly into autonomous action
    And the gap between knowing and doing is closed through skill encoding
